HEADWORD: Pietist
<hw>Pi"e*tist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. G.
<ets>pietist</ets>, F. <ets>pi⟦eacute⟧tiste</ets>. See
<er>Piety</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>One of a class of
religious reformers in Germany in the 17th century who sought to revive
declining piety in the Protestant churches; -- often applied as a term
of reproach to those who make a display of religious feeling. Also used
adjectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

